# Extractor (Stage 1)

When the user invokes **`Extract Call Records for [CustomerName]`** (or clearly the same intent), follow **`docs/ai/playbooks/extract-call-records.md`** end-to-end.

**`_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E override (test-only):** when this extraction is part of **`Run E2E Test Customer`** for **`_TEST_CUSTOMER`**, skip approval pauses and execute **`write_call_record`** directly. See **`docs/ai/playbooks/e2e-test-customer.md`**.

## Authority and validation

- **Canonical schema:** `docs/project_spec.md` **§7.1 Per-Call Record**. On-disk validation is enforced by **`prestonotes_mcp/call_records.py`** (`CALL_RECORD_SCHEMA`, `validate_call_record_object`). Every record you assemble **must** pass that schema or MCP **`write_call_record`** will fail.
- **Call types:** Only these **`call_type`** values are allowed: `discovery`, `technical_deep_dive`, `campaign`, `exec_qbr`, `poc_readout`, `renewal`, `internal`. Classification rubric: **`docs/ai/references/call-type-taxonomy.md`**.
- **`call_id`:** Must match the **`write_call_record`** argument and **`record_json.call_id`** exactly. Safe basename only (letters, digits, `._-`); no path segments. Prefer **`YYYY-MM-DD-<type>-<n>`** aligned with the filename stem when one meeting maps to one transcript file.
- **`raw_transcript_ref`:** Basename of the per-call **`.txt`** source (e.g. `2026-04-15-chain-guard.txt`), not a full path.

## Field discipline (schema v2 — TASK-051 §A)

- **`participants`:** Only people who appear or are named in the transcript; use `role` / `company` when stated or clearly inferable — otherwise empty string or omit optional keys if your JSON still validates. Do not fabricate executives.
- **`verbatim_quotes`:** At most **3** entries; each **`quote`** must be a **substring** of the transcript (trim whitespace only) and **≤ 280 chars**. `speaker` MUST match a `participants[].name` — `write_call_record` rejects orphan speakers and quotes not found in `raw_transcript_ref` under `MyNotes/Customers/<Customer>/Transcripts/`.
- **`challenges_mentioned`:** `id` matches `^ch-[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]{1,40}$` (kebab); `description` ≥ 10 chars; **`status`** follows §7.4 vocabulary (`identified`, `acknowledged`, `in_progress`, `resolved`, `reopened`, `stalled`). Prefer meaningful kebab ids (`ch-splunk-budget-freeze`, `ch-champion-exit`) over opaque counters like `ch-001`. Use stable ids across calls when the same issue recurs so UCN / `challenge-lifecycle.json` can reconcile.
- **`key_topics`:** `minItems: 1`, each item ≥ 3 chars, **unique per call**. Never a hardcoded placeholder.
- **`products_discussed`:** Enum `Wiz Cloud | Wiz Sensor | Wiz Defend | Wiz DSPM | Wiz CIEM | Wiz Code | Wiz CLI | Wiz Sensor POV`, or `Other: <name>` for non-Wiz products. Pick per-call; never a constant across all records in a corpus.
- **`action_items[].owner`:** Named individual when the transcript names one; `"SE"` only when the transcript itself says `SE:` and no person is attached.
- **`sentiment`:** Enum `positive | neutral | cautious | negative`. A call dominated by budget freeze / champion exit is at minimum `cautious`, not `positive`.
- **`deltas_from_prior_call`:** **Read the prior 3 call-records** via `read_call_records` before drafting the current one so this field reflects real state change (`in_progress → stalled`, `pursue → purchased`, etc.). `[]` only when nothing actually changed.
- **v2 optional richness arrays:** `goals_mentioned[]`, `risks_mentioned[]`, `metrics_cited[]`, `stakeholder_signals[]`. Populate from a light MEDDPICC pass; empty arrays are valid but ≥ 3 empties force a downgrade of `extraction_confidence` (`high → medium`; ≥ 5 empties → `low`). Accept the downgrade rather than fabricate.
- **`extraction_confidence`:** `high` | `medium` | `low`. The MCP writer mutates this in-place per the emptiness rule above; document the downgrade reason in run notes.

## Banned defaults (hard reject)

The MCP write path uses `BANNED_CALL_RECORD_DEFAULTS` in `prestonotes_mcp/call_records.py` — a SEPARATE list from `FORBIDDEN_EVIDENCE_TERMS` in `prestonotes_mcp/journey.py`. The journey list is harness-vocabulary for ledger / lifecycle evidence strings; the call-record list is stub-fallback fingerprints observed during the TASK-051 regression:

- `ch-stub` — never use this `challenges_mentioned[].id`.
- `Fixture narrative` — never use this description.
- `E2E fixture` — never use this `key_topics` item.

Also avoid: hardcoded `products_discussed` lists, identical `sentiment` across materially different calls, generic `action_items[].owner` (`"SE"`) when a named owner exists. Extract or downgrade — the writer will bounce stub values.

## Sales discovery anchor (MEDDPICC)

Run a light MEDDPICC pass on every transcript and route hits to the v2 arrays — **not** to `summary_one_liner` (format frozen; indexed downstream):

| MEDDPICC letter | v2 field |
|---|---|
| **M**etrics | `metrics_cited[]` |
| **E**conomic buyer / **C**hampion / **D**ecision makers | `stakeholder_signals[]` |
| **G**oals (from D, I) | `goals_mentioned[]` |
| **P**ain / risk / blockers | `risks_mentioned[]` |

## Sentiment (vocabulary)

Use one of: **`positive`**, **`neutral`**, **`cautious`**, **`negative`**. Pick the best fit from customer tone and outcomes discussed.

## Sources

- **Preferred:** One meeting per file under **`MyNotes/Customers/[Customer]/Transcripts/`** (Granola export pattern `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.txt` per `scripts/granola-sync.py`).
- **`_MASTER_TRANSCRIPT_*.txt`:** Do **not** load entire masters into context. If only masters exist, stop and tell the user to run per-call export / split first, **unless** they explicitly instruct a **bounded** excerpt (max length stated in the playbook step).

## Output

Produce **compact JSON** objects ready for **`write_call_record`**. For normal (non-E2E) runs: after user approval, write **one file per meeting**. For the `_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E override, execute without waiting for approval.

