## Challenge lifecycle write rules (TASK-048)

Every **`update_challenge_state`** call UCN makes MUST obey the following. Three of these are also hard-enforced MCP-side (future date, history regression, forbidden evidence vocabulary — see **`prestonotes_mcp/journey.py`**). The rest are extractor-side only; the MCP write path intentionally does not regex-check them, so the extractor is the sole enforcement point.

1. **`transitioned_at` is the call date, not the run date.** Read it from the cited transcript's header (`DATE:` line, ISO form). If the transcript does not expose a parseable call date, the extractor **does not write** that transition and emits one log line: `skip update_challenge_state ch=<id> reason=unknown_call_date`. UCN continues with the rest of its work.
2. **Evidence format (one transition = one call).** `evidence` MUST be structured as `<YYYY-MM-DD> <call-topic-short>: "<direct quote, ≤ 160 chars>"`. No paraphrase. No multi-call blobs. No meta-process language.
3. **Honor explicit state directives verbatim.** If a transcript contains a directive from the customer (regex-detectable family: *"treat as X, not Y"*, *"track as X instead of Y"*, *"mark it resolved"*, *"this is no longer stalled"*, *"resolved after the patch cycle"*), the extractor uses the directive's target state verbatim and cites that same line as evidence.
4. **Resolved sweep at end of run.** After writing all transitions from the current run, for each challenge whose current state is `in_progress` or `stalled`, scan the newest-in-lookback transcript for explicit unblock language (*"no longer stalled"*, *"resolved"*, *"shipped"*, *"done"*, *"we got it"*). If found, write a `resolved` transition at that transcript's call date.
5. **Collapse rule (no no-op transitions).** Do not call `update_challenge_state` if the proposed `(state, at)` tuple equals the last entry already in `history` for that `challenge_id`.
6. **Split rule.** If a single extracted challenge actually contains two distinct subjects and the transcript contains explicit split language (*"keep Splunk renewal separate from the budget blocker"*), open two ids (e.g. `ch-soc-budget` and `ch-splunk-integration`) and write them separately.
7. **Forbidden evidence vocabulary.** `evidence` MUST NOT contain any term from `FORBIDDEN_EVIDENCE_TERMS` in **`prestonotes_mcp/journey.py`** (case-insensitive substring match — that module is the single source of truth; the list in **`.cursor/rules/11-e2e-test-customer-trigger.mdc`** is the operator-facing mirror). The MCP write path rejects violations with `{"error": "evidence contains forbidden harness vocabulary", "field": "evidence", "matched": "<term>"}`; avoid the round-trip by scrubbing before calling.

## Ledger cell extraction (TASK-049)

Every UCN run that reaches Step 11 builds one **schema v3** row for `append_ledger_row`. The column-by-column extraction rules below complement the table in `docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md` Step 11 and are enforced partly by the MCP writer (`prestonotes_mcp/ledger.py`) and partly by the extractor.

1. **One transcript line per free-text cell (internal citation).** Every free-text cell you populate (`coverage`, `goals_delta`, `tools_delta`, `stakeholders_delta`, `value_realized`, `next_critical_event`) must trace back to **one** specific line in a transcript covered by this run. Keep the line pointer in your working state / reasoning — do **not** embed the citation in the cell. This is the same evidence discipline that already applies to `update_challenge_state`.
2. **No harness vocabulary in any cell.** Free-text cells, enum cells, and id-list fragments MUST NOT contain any term from **`FORBIDDEN_EVIDENCE_TERMS`** in `prestonotes_mcp/journey.py` (the same SSoT TASK-047/TASK-048 already point at; the operator-facing mirror is `.cursor/rules/11-e2e-test-customer-trigger.mdc` "Artifact hygiene"). The MCP write path rejects violations with `{"ok": false, "error": "ledger cell contains forbidden harness vocabulary", "field": "<col>", "matched": "<term>"}`; scrub before calling rather than round-tripping.
3. **`run_date` = today; `call_type` = most salient.** `run_date` is the UCN run date (ISO `YYYY-MM-DD`). `call_type` is the single best-fit enum value across the transcripts covered by the run (`qbr | exec_readout | product_demo | commercial_close | technical_pov | champion_1on1 | kickoff | other`). Enum cells (`call_type`, `account_health`, `sentiment`, `wiz_license_evidence_quality`) may only contain defined enum values — the writer rejects anything else.
4. **`wiz_score` — verbatim or empty, never inferred.** Populate `wiz_score` only with the **verbatim integer** a customer stated in an in-scope transcript (0..100). If no transcript states a number, leave the key out (empty cell). Do not compute, estimate, or synthesize a score — the writer accepts `int` or absent; anything else is rejected.
5. **`value_realized` quantified when evidence allows.** If **any** in-scope transcript contains at least one quantified element (regex-family `\$\d | \d+% | \d+\s*(workloads|CVEs|findings|weeks|hours|alerts)`), the `value_realized` cell MUST include at least one such element. If no in-scope transcript contains a quantified element, free-text narrative is fine. This is an extractor-side rule; the MCP writer does not regex-check it.
6. **Challenge columns are derived, not extracted.** Never populate `challenges_new`, `challenges_in_progress`, `challenges_stalled`, or `challenges_resolved` from transcript text. Derive them from `read_challenge_lifecycle` output for the customer. UCN Step 11 has the exact derivation rules.

## Per-section GDoc extraction (TASK-050 §C)

Every UCN run MUST visit the **15 populatable GDoc fields** below. For each field, the planner either proposes a mutation backed by an in-lookback transcript quote OR records a skip with one of four reasons: `no_in_scope_transcript_signal`, `same_as_current_entry`, `evidence_below_confidence_threshold`, `section_off_by_opt_out`. Skip accounting is what the UCN writer surfaces in the `appendix.agent_run_log` entry (TASK-050 §F). Fields not listed here (e.g. `cloud_environment.csp_regions`, `cloud_environment.idp_sso`, `cloud_environment.sizing`, `challenge_tracker` rows) retain their existing Step 9 / daily UCN rules — they are covered by the four planner coverage guard fields and the table-row policies elsewhere in this rule.

1. **`company_overview.free_text`** — industry + size + platform stance. Quote one transcript line.
2. **`contacts.free_text`** — every **customer-side** (and materially relevant) person named in in-lookback transcripts; include role if stated; flag departures (e.g. champion exit) explicitly. **When `call-records/*.json` exists**, use `participants[]` and `stakeholder_signals[]` from those records as structured support for the same calls — the agent composes `append_with_history` mutations in UCN Step 8 per `docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md` and `docs/ai/gdoc-customer-notes/mutations-account-summary-tab.md` (Contacts section). Do **not** replace that with ad-hoc `/tmp` JSON or non-playbook mutation sidecars.
3. **`org_structure.free_text`** — identity hub, tenant structure, acquisition relationships.
4. **`cloud_environment.platforms`** — `tools_list` entries for container orchestrator, compute, serverless.
5. **`cloud_environment.devops_vcs`** — CI/CD systems named in transcripts.
6. **`cloud_environment.security_tools`** — SIEMs, agents, CDRs named in transcripts, including retired ones with `(retired)` suffix.
7. **`cloud_environment.ticketing`** — ticketing tools named.
8. **`use_cases.free_text`** — one entry per distinct use case covered by a call.
9. **`workflows.free_text`** — one entry per distinct workflow/process covered.
10. **`accomplishments.free_text`** — one entry per quantified customer win (workload counts, retired tools, score deltas, acquisition visibility, challenge resolutions).
11. **`account_motion_metadata.exec_buyer`** — named exec sponsor.
12. **`account_motion_metadata.champion`** — named champion.
13. **`account_motion_metadata.technical_owner`** — named technical owner / SE counterpart.
14. **`account_motion_metadata.sensor_coverage_pct`** — numeric only, verbatim from transcript.
15. **`account_motion_metadata.critical_issues_open`** — numeric only, verbatim from transcript.

**`account_motion_metadata.mttr_days`** and **`account_motion_metadata.monthly_reporting_hours`** are populated only when a transcript states the number explicitly; otherwise skip with `no_in_scope_transcript_signal`.

The `STRICT_METADATA_FIELDS` constraint from `docs/ai/gdoc-customer-notes/mutations-account-metadata-tab.md` still applies to `exec_buyer` / `champion` / `technical_owner` — only write them when explicitly stated in source evidence; do not infer from role or title hints.

## Challenge Tracker row discipline (TASK-048 §B.1)

The **same "call date wins over run date" rule** applies to a **second write path** that bypasses `update_challenge_state`: UCN's GDoc mutation plan writes **Challenge Tracker** rows directly via **`write_doc`**, and those rows have their own `date` column and `notes_references` evidence string. **`write_doc`** is a generic doc writer and does not validate these — enforcement is extractor-side preflight only.

1. **Challenge Tracker row `date` column** MUST be the ISO call date of the most recent transcript that touched this challenge, **not** the run date.
2. **`notes_references` `Evidence: YYYY-MM-DD` dates** MUST cite ISO dates that exist in the customer's `MyNotes/Customers/<Customer>/Transcripts/` folder. Preflight: for every `YYYY-MM-DD` referenced in `notes_references`, verify a transcript file with that date prefix exists on disk. If the check fails, skip the row and emit `skip challenge_tracker_row ch=<id> reason=evidence_date_not_in_corpus`.
3. **Forbidden vocabulary.** `notes_references` MUST NOT contain any term from `FORBIDDEN_EVIDENCE_TERMS` (same list as above). Scrub before the mutation plan is built.
4. **Parity with lifecycle writes.** Every `update_challenge_state` row in Block A should have a matching Challenge Tracker row in Block B whose `date` and `notes_references` dates come from the same transcript(s). If you cannot satisfy §B.1 #1–#3 for a row, drop the lifecycle row too rather than persist an inconsistent pair (mirrors the lifecycle–tracker parity guard in **`.cursor/rules/20-orchestrator.mdc`** step 7).
